00:25:35.936 --> 00:25:38.346
[LAUGHTER]

00:25:38.346 --> 00:25:40.690
JOHN TAYLOR: Chapter
31, Legal Age.

00:25:40.690 --> 00:25:44.500
One thing I discovered on tour
in 1981 was that girls, in all

00:25:44.500 --> 00:25:47.860
languages, like taking
drugs with me.

00:25:47.860 --> 00:25:50.370
Even though I had a girlfriend
back home, my horror of lonely

00:25:50.370 --> 00:25:52.920
hotel rooms meant I would go
to any lengths to avoid

00:25:52.920 --> 00:25:54.590
sleeping in them alone.

00:25:54.590 --> 00:25:56.920
Coke, I was beginning to
realize, was an effective

00:25:56.920 --> 00:25:59.980
insurance policy against
that eventuality.

00:25:59.980 --> 00:26:01.500
I'd been a nerd at school.

00:26:01.500 --> 00:26:03.960
I wasn't a jock or an
intellectual, and I'd never

00:26:03.960 --> 00:26:06.500
had a regular girlfriend
as a teenager.

00:26:06.500 --> 00:26:09.040
Now I only had to wink in a
girl's direction in a hotel

00:26:09.040 --> 00:26:12.180
lobby, backstage, or at a record
company party, and I

00:26:12.180 --> 00:26:14.590
have company until
the morning.

00:26:14.590 --> 00:26:17.030
So what's the problem,
you might ask?

00:26:17.030 --> 00:26:19.050
Well, the trouble is-- and I
didn't figure this out until I

00:26:19.050 --> 00:26:20.080
was almost 40--

00:26:20.080 --> 00:26:22.320
that there's something about an
intimate encounter of that

00:26:22.320 --> 00:26:24.430
nature with someone you
barely know that

00:26:24.430 --> 00:26:26.250
jars against the spirit.

00:26:26.250 --> 00:26:28.410
You want it, but it doesn't
feel quite right.

00:26:28.410 --> 00:26:30.870
And when you start doing it
night after night, week in,

00:26:30.870 --> 00:26:33.790
week out, your ideas about
love and sex begin to get

00:26:33.790 --> 00:26:35.270
somewhat distorted.

00:26:35.270 --> 00:26:38.650
And jumping into bed like porn
star Johnny is not as easy as

00:26:38.650 --> 00:26:41.540
you might imagine, especially
with someone whose first name

00:26:41.540 --> 00:26:43.250
you're not even sure of.

00:26:43.250 --> 00:26:45.840
You feel awkward, or
at least I do.

00:26:45.840 --> 00:26:48.200
Maybe it was some residue
of Catholic guilt.

00:26:48.200 --> 00:26:49.930
Plain old common decency?

00:26:49.930 --> 00:26:52.360
Hadn't mother taught me
something about this?

00:26:52.360 --> 00:26:55.090
The drugs and the alcohol served
to take away all those

00:26:55.090 --> 00:26:58.270
doubts, plus any inhibitions
or insecurities I

00:26:58.270 --> 00:26:59.780
or she might have.

00:26:59.780 --> 00:27:01.410
I didn't want to be lonely,
and the drugs

00:27:01.410 --> 00:27:03.680
ensured I never was.

00:27:03.680 --> 00:27:06.620
I'm a pinup on thousands of
bedroom walls, but the fear of

00:27:06.620 --> 00:27:10.240
loneliness is turning
me into a cokehead.

00:27:10.240 --> 00:27:11.950
Of absolute necessity
for any touring

00:27:11.950 --> 00:27:13.320
musician is the itinerary.

00:27:13.320 --> 00:27:15.740
It usually comes as a gift from
the tour manager on the

00:27:15.740 --> 00:27:17.170
last day of rehearsal.

00:27:17.170 --> 00:27:19.230
Depending on the length of the
tour about to be undertaken,

00:27:19.230 --> 00:27:21.510
it could cover any length
of time between one

00:27:21.510 --> 00:27:22.950
week and two months.

00:27:22.950 --> 00:27:24.520
Page one lists the principals--

00:27:24.520 --> 00:27:26.030
the inner circle--

00:27:26.030 --> 00:27:28.670
the crew who are going to get
the show around the world.

00:27:28.670 --> 00:27:31.540
All the numbers to call if in
trouble are listed there-- the

00:27:31.540 --> 00:27:33.130
management, the agencies,
the travel

00:27:33.130 --> 00:27:35.390
agents, the local promoters.

00:27:35.390 --> 00:27:38.570
Then follows a page by page
account of the destinations.

00:27:38.570 --> 00:27:40.620
October 3rd, Chicago.

00:27:40.620 --> 00:27:42.430
Band hotel, Ambassador East.

00:27:42.430 --> 00:27:44.250
Crew hotel, Crown Hyatt.

00:27:44.250 --> 00:27:46.790
Venue, Park West, and
so on and so on.

00:27:46.790 --> 00:27:49.110
I'd not noticed right away that
in the left hand corner

00:27:49.110 --> 00:27:50.370
of each page of the US

00:27:50.370 --> 00:27:51.930
itinerary, there was a number--

00:27:51.930 --> 00:27:55.080
usually 18, 20, or 21.

00:27:55.080 --> 00:27:57.140
It was months before I was
let in on the secret.

00:27:57.140 --> 00:27:59.240
The numbers referred to the
legal age for sexual

00:27:59.240 --> 00:28:03.170
intercourse in that
particular state.

00:28:03.170 --> 00:28:05.460
The other necessity for the
touring musician is the day

00:28:05.460 --> 00:28:08.750
sheet, usually slipped under the
hotel room door while the

00:28:08.750 --> 00:28:10.310
occupant is still asleep.

00:28:10.310 --> 00:28:13.330
Regardless of the degree of
befuddlement, the day sheet

00:28:13.330 --> 00:28:15.670
information was always
quite clear.

00:28:15.670 --> 00:28:21.790
Today is October 3rd, it is
Friday, you are in Chicago.

00:28:21.790 --> 00:28:23.830
Today is a show day.

00:28:23.830 --> 00:28:25.620
Sound check is at 4:00 PM.

00:28:25.620 --> 00:28:29.128
You almost expected it to
say, your name is John.

00:28:29.128 --> 00:28:31.080
[LAUGHTER]

00:28:31.080 --> 00:28:33.060
ADAM STEWART: That's awesome.

00:28:33.060 --> 00:28:36.550
So I think at that point in
the book, too, you start

00:28:36.550 --> 00:28:38.130
talking a little bit more, and
it comes up even in that

00:28:38.130 --> 00:28:40.580
chapter, this kind of notion
of loneliness.

00:28:40.580 --> 00:28:43.760
And it's now kind of being
equated to drugs and alcohol

00:28:43.760 --> 00:28:47.940
becoming a larger part
of your life.

00:28:47.940 --> 00:28:49.930
Was that a cause and effect?

00:28:49.930 --> 00:28:51.930
Was it the loneliness and then
what you were kind of feeling

00:28:51.930 --> 00:28:54.070
on the road that led
you to that point?

00:28:54.070 --> 00:28:55.220
JOHN TAYLOR: Well, I'm still
figuring it out, really.

00:28:55.220 --> 00:28:57.780
I mean, getting to write a book
like this, you really do

00:28:57.780 --> 00:29:00.645
analyze your behavior,
and the whys.

00:29:04.360 --> 00:29:05.920
I was the guy in the band
that just didn't

00:29:05.920 --> 00:29:07.160
have the off switch.

00:29:07.160 --> 00:29:09.530
I mean, it could be 5:00 in the
morning and everybody else

00:29:09.530 --> 00:29:11.760
was turning in, because
we had a travel day or

00:29:11.760 --> 00:29:12.420
whatever the next--

00:29:12.420 --> 00:29:15.600
I'd just be getting started.

00:29:15.600 --> 00:29:17.560
And you become the guy.

00:29:17.560 --> 00:29:19.370
We've all got one
in our family.

00:29:19.370 --> 00:29:21.310
Every family's got one.

00:29:21.310 --> 00:29:23.690
Uncle Jake just doesn't
know how to put

00:29:23.690 --> 00:29:25.070
the plug in the jug.

00:29:25.070 --> 00:29:26.490
Just doesn't know
when to stop.

00:29:26.490 --> 00:29:31.360
And when you are that guy, you
start getting a lot of shame.

00:29:31.360 --> 00:29:34.440
Over the years, you're
the hung over one.

00:29:34.440 --> 00:29:39.396
You're the butt of the joke.

00:29:39.396 --> 00:29:42.740
And I'm not sure what that
loneliness was about.

00:29:42.740 --> 00:29:45.280
I think it was a combination
of things.

00:29:45.280 --> 00:29:46.530
I mean, fame is very--

00:29:49.040 --> 00:29:50.640
you've got a lot of
people around

00:29:50.640 --> 00:29:55.170
you giving you attention.

00:29:55.170 --> 00:29:57.150
It's very addictive.

00:29:57.150 --> 00:30:01.610
I mean, it's very hard
to turn off from.

00:30:01.610 --> 00:30:07.210
And I found it to be quite an
insecure world, actually.

00:30:07.210 --> 00:30:12.240
We had a couple of good years,
but then paranoia set in, and

00:30:12.240 --> 00:30:14.210
the drugs didn't help that.

00:30:14.210 --> 00:30:16.090
Hangover wont'--

00:30:16.090 --> 00:30:19.060
when you're late for the
meeting, what's the first

00:30:19.060 --> 00:30:19.940
thing you think?

00:30:19.940 --> 00:30:22.510
What have they been
saying about me?

00:30:22.510 --> 00:30:24.170
ADAM STEWART: There's some
pretty harrowing stories in

00:30:24.170 --> 00:30:24.730
the book, you know?

00:30:24.730 --> 00:30:26.230
All nighters, and--

00:30:26.230 --> 00:30:26.920
JOHN TAYLOR: What's that?

00:30:26.920 --> 00:30:30.720
ADAM STEWART: All nighters,
and some wild times.

00:30:30.720 --> 00:30:34.300
When did you realize that
you had a problem?

00:30:34.300 --> 00:30:35.980
When did you decide to do
something about it?

00:30:35.980 --> 00:30:39.160
JOHN TAYLOR: Well, I
think any of us--

00:30:39.160 --> 00:30:40.370
when do you realize
you're an addict?

00:30:40.370 --> 00:30:43.490
When do you realize you're
addicted to shopping or

00:30:43.490 --> 00:30:44.220
